The South South chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has commiserated with President Muhammadu Buhari over the death of his Chief of Staff, Mallam Abba Kyari. While condoling President Buhari, the chapter also sympathized with the immediate family and assured of continious prayers during this trying times In a statement by the National Vice Chairman South South, Ntufam Hilliard Eta, the chapter prayed for the repose of the departed soul. “On behalf of the entire zonal leadership of our great party, the APC, in the south south zone, I write to commiserate with His Excellency, President Muhammadu Buhari, GCGR on the sad news of the passage of Chief of Staff to the President, Late Mallam Abba Kyari. “Mr President, this is a very trying moment for you, please be strong and be sure that our prayers are with you. “I also sympathize with the immediate family of Mallam Abba Kyari. As I know that the deceased did his very best for our country and in his capacity as the President’s Chief of staff, it my prayers that comfort his immediate family and also grant the soul of the departed eternal rest.”